D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmount-everest-death-zone-what-happens-to-body-2019-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehigh%20altitudes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20well%20as%20evidence%20of%20active%20burrows%2C%20Storz%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20still%20a%20lot%20left%20to%20discover%2C%26quot%3B%20Storz%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20live%20mouse%20and%20the%20summit%20mummies%20%26quot%3Brepresent%20the%20highest%20altitude%20physical%20records%20of%20mammals%20in%20the%20world.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cell.com%2Fcurrent-biology%2Ffulltext%2FS0960-9822(23)01161-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudy%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20published%20Monday%20in%20the%20journal%20Current%20Biology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ECould%20these%20mice%20have%20special%20adaptations%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EStorz%20stumbled%20upon%20the%20first%20mouse%20mummy%20by%20chance.%20Soon%20he%20and%20his%20colleagues%20were%20finding%20more%20and%20more%20freeze-dried%20mouse%20cadavers%20in%20the%20crevices%20of%20volcanic%20rock.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22man%20in%20yellow%20windbreaker%20jacket%20and%20grey%20wide%20brimmed%20hat%20reaches%20a%20trekking%20pole%20into%20a%20crevice%20under%20a%20rock%20outcropping%20atop%20a%20barren%20mountain%20landscape%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6538131396f7540cd064531e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221875%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJay%20Storz%20excavates%20mouse%20mummies%20on%20the%20summit%20of%20Volc%C3%A1n%20P%C3%BAlar%20in%20northern%20Chile.%3Cp%3EMario%20P%C3%A9rez%20Mamani%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20mummies%20were%20mostly%20a%20few%20decades%20old%2C%20but%20some%20dated%20back%20several%20centuries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGenomic%20analysis%20of%20the%20mummies%20showed%20that%20they%20were%20equal%20numbers%20of%20male%20and%20female%20mice%20and%20that%20some%20were%20closely%20related.%20That%20suggests%20the%20mice%20actually%20established%20communities%20at%20the%20tops%20of%20the%20volcanoes%2C%20rather%20than%20a%20few%20individuals%20randomly%20climbing%20up%20there.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStorz%20told%20Insider%20that%20the%20only%20advantage%20he%20can%20think%20of%20for%20the%20mountaineering%20mice%20is%20that%20there%20are%20no%20predators%20on%20top%20of%20the%20volcanoes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20the%20mice's%20motives%2C%20it's%20a%20mystery%20how%20they%20manage%20to%20survive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWell-trained%20mountain%20climbers%20can%20tolerate%20such%20extreme%20elevations%20during%20a%20one-day%20summit%20attempt%2C%20but%20the%20fact%20that%20mice%20are%20actually%20living%20at%20such%20elevations%20demonstrates%20that%20we%20have%20underestimated%20the%20physiological%20tolerances%20of%20small%20mammals%2C%26quot%3B%20Storz%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eurekalert.org%2Fnews-releases%2F1005132%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estatement%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20comparing%20the%20summit%20environment%20to%20Mars.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20scientists%20are%20now%20looking%20for%20signs%20of%20physiological%20adaptations%20that%20may%20allow%20these%20mice%20to%20survive%20at%20high%20elevations%20with%20low%20oxygen%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20collected%20mice%20from%20different%20elevations%20and%20are%20now%20experimentally%20exposing%20them%20to%20low%20oxygen%20to%20see%20whether%20the%20extreme-altitude%20mice%20show%20any%20unique%20physiology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStorz's%20team%20is%20also%20continuing%20to%20search%20the%20volcano%20tops%20for%20signs%20of%20mice%2C%20living%20or%20mummified.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhether%20it's%20the%20top%20of%20the%20highest%20mountains%20or%20the%20darkest%20depths%20of%20the%20ocean%2C%20it%20is%20always%20exciting%20to%20discover%20animals%20living%20in%20places%20where%20nobody%20expects%20anything%20to%20be%20living%2C%26