rican-American%20staffer%20on%20Capitol%20Hill%20in%20US%20history.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20died%20on%20October%2025%20after%20a%20nearly%2060-year%20career%20in%20the%20Senate.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EBowman%20first%20arrived%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20in%201944%20as%20a%20runaway%20and%20worked%20as%20a%20sweeper%20on%20the%20Capitol's%20steps.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EBertie%20Bowman%2C%20the%20longest-serving%20African-American%20staffer%20on%20Capitol%20Hill%20in%20history%2C%20died%20at%2092%20years%20old%20on%20Wednesday%20morning.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAndrew%20Desiderio%2C%20a%20reporter%20for%20Punchbowl%20News%2C%20first%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FAndrewDesiderio%2Fstatus%2F1717186892687458334%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20Bowman's%20death%20was%20announced%20by%20Sen.%20Ben%20Cardin%20of%20Maryland%20during%20a%20Senate%20Foreign%20Relations%20Committee%20meeting%20on%20Wednesday.%20A%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20committee%20confirmed%20the%20news.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHerbert%20%26quot%3BBertie%26quot%3B%20Bowman%20was%20born%20in%20Summerton%2C%20a%20small%20town%20in%20South%20Carolina%2C%20in%201931.%20Like%20many%20families%20during%20the%20Great%20Depression%2C%20the%20Bowmans%20struggled%20financially.%20Bowman%20recalled%20in%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.penguinrandomhouse.com%2Fbooks%2F16715%2Fstep-by-step-by-bertie-bowman%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ememoir%3C%2Fa%3E%20%26quot%3BStep%20by%20Step%26quot%3B%20that%20%26quot%3Bthe%20wind%20would%20whistle%20through%20the%20wooden%20boards%20of%20the%20house%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20winter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%2014%20Bowman%20children%20worked%20on%20their%20family's%20farm%2C%20waking%20up%20before%20dawn%20every%20day%20to%20complete%20morning%20chores%20before%20walking%20three%20miles%20to%20school.%20%26quot%3BThe%20white%20children%2C%20in%20buses%2C%20passed%20us%20on%20the%20road%20to%20their%20well-equipped%20classrooms%20and%20modern%20textbooks%2C%26quot%3B%20Bowman%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20chance%20encounter%20with%20a%20senator%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBowman%20dreamed%20of%20escaping%20the%20grueling%20life%20on%20the%20farm%20and%20his%20father's%20rule%20of%20law.%20He%20saw%20a%20glimmer%20of%20possibility%20in%201944%20when%20he%20met%20a%20senator%20from%20South%20Carolina%2C%20Burnet%20Maybank%2C%20who%20invited%20crowds%20gathered%20at%20a%20local%20store%20to%20%26quot%3Bdrop%20by%26quot%3B%20and%20see%20him%20if%20they%20were%20ever%20in%20Washington%2C%20DC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen-13-year-old%20Bowman%20approached%20Maybank%20as%20the%20senator%20was%20about%20to%20get%20into%20his%20car%20and%20asked%20if%20he%20was%20also%20invited%20to%20visit%20his%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20senator%20leaned%20over%20and%20replied%20graciously%2C%20'Certainly%2C%20my%20boy%2C'%26quot%3B%20Bowman%20recalled.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20idea%20of%20leaving%20Summerton%20and%20%26quot%3Bgoing%20up%20the%20road%26quot%3B%20became%20Bowman's%20obsession%2C%20and%20he%20began%20to%20plan%20his%20exit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223518%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Former%20Senator%20Chris%20Dodd%2C%20D-Conn.%2C%20left%2C%20hugs%20Bertie%20Bowman%2C%20a%20staffer%20with%20the%20Senate%20Foreign%20Relations%20Committee%2C%20before%20a%20subcommittee%20hearing%20in%20Dirksen%20Building%20entitled%20%26quot%3BThe%20Peace%20Corps%2C%20The%20Next%20Fifty%20Years.%26quot%3B%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6539667e96f7540cd065bab5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222340%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFormer%20Senator%20Chris%20Dodd%20hugs%20Bowman%20before%20a%20subcommittee%20hearing%20in%20October%202011.%3Cp%3ETom%20Williams%2FRoll%20Call%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EFrom%20janitor%20to%20congressional%20staffer%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20nights%20later%2C%20Bowman%2