rove%20traffic%20flow%20and%20safety.%20They%20offer%20several%20advantages%20over%20conventional%20intersections%20controlled%20by%20traffic%20signals%20or%20stop%20signs%2C%20but%20by%20far%20the%20most%20important%20one%20is%20safety.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20research%20transportation%20engineering%2C%20particularly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcommuting-by-car-is-hurting-peoples-mental-health-2023-7%5C%22%3Etraffic%20safety%20and%20traffic%20operations%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Some%20of%20my%20past%20studies%20have%20examined%20the%20safety%20and%20operational%20effects%20of%20installing%20roundabouts%20at%20an%20intersection.%20I've%20also%20compared%20the%20performance%20of%20roundabouts%20versus%20stop-controlled%20intersections.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20brief%20history%20of%20roundabouts%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221883%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Paris%20Gate%20Monument%20(Porte%20de%20Paris)%2C%20view%20from%20the%20Belfry%20of%20Lille%20City%20Hall%20in%20october%2C%20Lille%2C%20North%20of%20France%20-%20stock%20photo%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6539638196f7540cd065b3ae%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221412%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERoundabouts%20used%20to%20be%20more%20popular%20in%20Europe%20than%20in%20the%20US.%3Cp%3EPierre%20Longnus%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20early%20as%20the%201700s%2C%20some%20city%20planners%20proposed%20and%20even%20constructed%20circular%20places%2C%20sites%20where%20roads%20converged%2C%20like%20the%20Circus%20in%20Bath%2C%20England%2C%20and%20the%20Place%20Charles%20de%20Gaulle%20in%20France.%20In%20the%20U.S.%2C%20architect%20Pierre%20L'Enfant%20built%20several%20into%20his%20design%20for%20Washington%2C%20DC%2C%20These%20circles%20were%20the%20predecessors%20to%20roundabouts.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201903%2C%20French%20architect%20and%20influential%20urban%20planner%20Eug%C3%A8ne%20H%C3%A9nard%20was%20one%20of%20the%20first%20people%20who%20introduced%20the%20idea%20of%20moving%20traffic%20in%20a%20circle%20to%20control%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparis-set-citywide-speed-limit-reduce-pollution-improve-safety-2021-8%5C%22%3Ebusy%20intersections%20in%20Paris%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAround%20the%20same%20time%2C%20William%20Phelps%20Eno%2C%20an%20American%20businessman%20known%20as%20the%20father%20of%20traffic%20safety%20and%20control%2C%20also%20proposed%20roundabouts%20to%20alleviate%20traffic%20congestion%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnew-york-city-losing-rental-housing-crisis-combine-apartments-2023-10%5C%22%3ENew%20York%20City%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20years%20that%20followed%2C%20a%20few%20other%20cities%20tried%20out%20a%20roundabout-like%20design%2C%20with%20varying%20levels%20of%20success.%20These%20roundabouts%20didn't%20have%20any%20sort%20of%20standardized%20design%20guidelines%2C%20and%20most%20of%20them%20were%20too%20large%20to%20be%20effective%20and%20efficient%2C%20as%20vehicles%20would%20enter%20at%20higher%20speeds%20without%20always%20yielding.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20birth%20of%20the%20modern%20roundabout%20came%20with%20yield-at-entry%20regulations%2C%20adopted%20in%20some%20towns%20in%20Great%20Britain%20in%20the%201950s.%20With%20yield-at-entry%20regulations%2C%20the%20vehicles%20entering%20the%20roundabout%20had%20to%20give%20way%20to%20vehicles%20already%20circulating%20in%20the%20roundabout.%20This%20was%20made%20a%20rule%20nationwide%20in%20the%20United%20Kingdom%20in%201966%2C%20then%20in%20France%20in%201983.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYield-at-entry%20meant%20vehicles%20drove%20through%20these%20modern%20roundabouts%20more%20slowly%2C%20and%20over%20the%20years%2C%20engineers%20began%20adding%20more%20features%20that%20made%20them%20look%20closer%20to%20how%20roundabouts%20do%20now.%20Many%20added%20pedestrian%20crossings%20and%20splitter%20islands%20%E2%80%93%20or%20raised%20curbs%20where%20vehicles%20entered%20and%20exited%20%E2%80%93%20which%20controlled%20the%20vehicles'%20speeds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEngineers%2C%20planners%20and%20decision-makers%20worldwide%20noticed%20that%20these%20roundabouts%20improved%20traffic%20flow%2C%20reduced%20congestion%20and%20improved%20safety%20at%20intersections.%20Roundabouts%20then%20spread%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnorway-tunnels-roundabouts-2016-8%5C%22%3Ethroughout%20Europe%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20Australia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThree%20decades%20later%2C%20modern%20roundabouts%20came%20to%20North%20America.%20The%20first%20modern%20roundabout%20in%20the%20U.S.%20was%20built%20in%20Summerlin%2C%20on%20the%20west%20side%20of%20Las%20Vegas%2C%20in%201990.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEver%20since%2C%20the%20construction%20of%20modern%20roundabouts%20in%20the%20U.S.%20has%20picked%20up%20steam.%20There%20are%20now%20about%2010%2C000%20roundabouts%20in%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhy%20use%20roundabouts%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22939%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Traffic%20Jam%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6539639b0487ff031cae5b0c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22469%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERoundabouts%20are%20supposed%20to%20help%20traffic%20flow%20more%20smoothly.%3Cp%3EChinaFotoPress%2F%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ERoundabouts%20likely%20caught%20on%20so%20quickly%20because%20they%20reduce%20the%20number%20of%20potential%20conflict%20points.%20A%20conflict%20point%20at%20an%20intersection%20is%20a%20location%20where%20the%20paths%20of%20two%20or%20more%20vehicles%20or%20road%20users%20cross%20or%20have%20the%20potential%20to%20cross.%20The%20more%20conflict%20points%2C%20the%20more%20likely%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdrivers-crash-into-us-storefronts-every-day-7-eleven-2023-2%5C%22%3Evehicles%20are%20to%20crash%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20roundabout%20has%20only%20eight%20potential%20conflict%20points%2C%20compared%20to%2032%20at%20a%20conventional%20four-way%20intersection.%20At%20roundabouts%2C%20vehicles%20don't%20cross%20each%20other%20at%20a%20right%20angle%2C%20and%20there%20are%20fewer%20points%20where%20vehicles%20merge%20or%20diverge%20into%20or%20away%20from%20each%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20roundabout's%20tight%20circle%20forces%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffourth-color-traffic-lights-streets-self-driving-robot-cars-trucks-2023-4%5C%22%3Eapproaching%20traffic%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20slow%20down%20and%20yield%20to%20circulating%20traffic%2C%20and%20then%20move%20smoothly%20around%20the%20central%20island.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20roundabouts%20have%20fewer%20stop-and-go%20issues%2C%20which%20reduces%20fuel%20consumption%20and%20vehicle%20emissions%20and%20allows%20drivers%20to%20perform%20U-turns%20more%20easily.%20Since%20traffic%20flows%20continuously%20at%20lower%20speeds%20in%20a%20roundabout%2C%20this%20continuous%20flow%20minimizes%20the%20need%20for%20vehicles%20to%20stop%2C%20which%20reduces%20congestion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Federal%20Highway%20Administration%20estimates%20that%20when%20a%20roundabout%20replaces%20a%20stop%20sign-controlled%20intersection%2C%20it%20reduces%20serious%20and%20fatal%20injury%20crashes%20by%2090%25%2C%20and%20when%20it%20replaces%20an%20intersection%20with%20a%20traffic%20light%2C%20it%20reduces%20serious%20and%20fatal%20injury%20crashes%20by%20nearly%2080%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhy%20do%20some%20places%20have%20more%20than%20others%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221998%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20aerial%20photo%20of%20Columbus%20Circle%20in%20New%20York%20City.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6539642b356802a56be3dff6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221499%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20East%20Coast%20of%20the%20US%20tend%20to%20has%20more%20roundabouts%20than%20the%20West%20Coast.%3Cp%3EOrbon%20Alija%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EEngineers%20and%20planners%20traditionally%20have%20installed%20roundabouts%20in%20intersections%20with%20severe%20congestion%20or%20a%20history%20of%20accidents.%20But%2C%20with%20public%20support%20and%20funding%2C%20they%20can%20get%20installed%20anywhere.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20roundabouts%20aren't%20needed%20in%20every%20intersection.%20In%20places%20where%20congestion%20isn't%20an%20issue%2C%20city%20planners%20tend%20not%20to%20push%20for%20them.%20For%20example%2C%20while%20there%20are%20%5Baround%20750%20roundabouts%5D%20in%20Florida%2C%20there%20are%20fewer%20than%2050%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhat-its-like-living-in-bismarck-north-dakota-2023-10%5C%22%3ENorth%20Dakota%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsouth-dakota-named-least-stressed-state-us-2022-10%5C%22%3ESouth%20Dakota%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwyoming-republican-says-christian-nationalism-has-hijacked-state-2023-5%5C%22%3EWyoming%3C%2Fa%3E%20combined.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERoundabouts%20have%20been%20gaining%20popularity%20in%20the%20U.S.%20in%20recent%20years%2C%20in%20part%20because%20the%20Federal%20Highway%20Administration%20recommends%20them%20as%20the%20safest%20option.%20Some%20states%2C%20like%20New%20York%20and%20Virginia%2C%20have%20adopted%20a%20%26quot%3Broundabout%20first%26quot%3B%20policy%2C%20where%20engineers%20default%20to%20using%20roundabouts%20where%20feasible%20when%20building%20or%20upgrading%20intersections.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202000%2C%20the%20U.S.%20only%20had%20356%20roundabouts.%20Over%20the%20past%20two%20decades%2C%20that%20number%20has%20grown%20to%20over%2010%2C000.%20Love%20them%20or%20hate%20them%2C%20the%20roundabout's%20widespread%20adoption%20suggests%20that%20these%20ci