%9D%20around%20India%E2%80%99s%20missions%20in%20Canada%20and%20indicated%20that%20if%20there%20is%20substantial%20%E2%80%9Cprogress%E2%80%9D%20in%20ensuring%20the%20safety%20of%20diplomats%2C%20the%20resumption%20of%20visa%20services%20could%20occur%20%E2%80%9Cvery%20soon%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20media%20statement%20issued%20by%20the%20high%20commission%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CAfter%20a%20considered%20review%20of%20the%20security%20situation%20that%20takes%20into%20account%20some%20recent%20Canadian%20measures%20in%20this%20regard%2C%20it%20has%20been%20decided%20to%20resume%20visa%20services%20for%20the%20following%20categories%20with%20effect%20from%20October%2026%2C%202023%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20development%20will%20come%20as%20a%20reprieve%20to%20Canadian%20citizens%20of%20Indian%20origin%2C%20who%20were%20unable%20to%20travel%20to%20India%20over%20the%20past%20month%20if%20they%20did%20not%20have%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fociservices.gov.in%2F%5C%22%3EOCI%20card%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20development%20comes%20just%20five%20days%20after%20Canada%20announced%20that%20it%20had%20withdrawn%2041%20diplomats%20from%20India%20and%20stopped%20in-person%20facilities%20at%20three%20consulates%20in%20the%20country%20after%20New%20Delhi%20sought%20%E2%80%98parity%E2%80%99%20in%20diplomatic%20staff.%20Ottawa%20said%20that%20visa%20processing%20times%20for%20Indian%20applicants%20would%20increase%20as%20a%20consequence.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20Wednesday%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cicnews.com%2F2023%2F10%2Fimmigration-minister-canada-expects-to-process-20000-indian-visas-by-end-of-2023-1040651.html%23gs.6u7pbc%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ECanadian%20immigration%20minister%20Marc%20Miller%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20told%20a%20parliamentary%20standing%20committee%20that%20out%20of%20the%2038%2C000%20visas%20for%20Indians%2C%20only%2020%2C000%20will%20now%20be%20processed%20by%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECanada%E2%80%99s%20immigration%20department%20foresees%20a%20backlog%20of%20about%2017%2C500%20Indian%20applications%20at%20the%20start%20of%202024.%20Out%20of%20the%2041%20diplomats%20who%20left%20India%2C%20about%20half%20were%20dealing%20with%20visa%20issues.%20Currently%2C%20there%20are%20just%20five%20immigration%20officials%20working%20in%20the%20Canadian%20high%20commission.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEarlier%2C%20Canada%E2%80%99s%20missions%20in%20India%20used%20to%20process%20around%2015%2C000%20visas%20a%20week%2C%20in%20total.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20India%20had%20publicly%20dismissed%20the%20allegations%20made%20by%20Trudeau%20in%20the%20House%20of%20Commons%2C%20it%20had%20sought%20%E2%80%9Cparity%E2%80%9D%20and%20furnished%20a%20list%20of%20names%20to%20the%20Canadian%20side%20whose%20diplomatic%20immunity%20would%20be%20revoked%20if%20they%20did%20not%20leave%20by%20October%2010%2C%20which%20was%20later%20extended%20by%2010%20days.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECanadian%20foreign%20minister%20M%C3%A9lanie%20Joly%20said%20India%20violated%20the%20Vienna%20Convention%20on%20Diplomatic%20Relations%20when%20it%20unilaterally%20threatened%20to%20remove%20the%20diplomatic%20immunity%20of%20accredited%20journalists.%20India%20has%2C%20however%2C%20claimed%20that%20its%20actions%20were%20as%20per%20Article%2011.1%20of%20the%201961%20treaty.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20also%20has%20publicly%20said%2C%20which%20Jaishankar%20reiterated%20on%20Sunday%2C%20that%20Canadian%20diplomats%20were%20interfering%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20internal%20affairs.%20However%2C%20India%20has%20never%20publicly%20mentioned%20any%20specific%20instances.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20the%20US%20and%20UK%20supported%20Canada%E2%80%99s%20contention%20that%20India%20had%20violated%20the%20Vienna%20Convention%2C%20New%20Zealand%20