2%3A%22'Baap%20of%20Chart'%20gave%20trade%20recos%20in%20the%20garb%20of%20education%20courses%2C%20mislead%20clients%2C%20alleges%20Sebi%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Fsebi-bars-finfluencer-from-securities-market-asks-to-disgorge-rs-17-cr-123102501080_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Fsebi-bars-finfluencer-from-securities-market-asks-to-disgorge-rs-17-cr-123102501080_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fmarkets%2Fnews%2Fsebi-bars-finfluencer-from-securities-market-asks-to-disgorge-rs-17-cr-123102501080_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bananas%20At%20Risk%20Of%20Extinction%20Due%20To%20Fungus%20Outbreak%2C%20Warn%20Scientists%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EExperts%20caution%20that%20the%20most%20widely%20consumed%20variety%20of%20bananas%20may%20be%20on%20the%20verge%20of%20extinction%20as%20a%20disease%20outbreak%20wreaks%20havoc%20on%20this%20potassium-rich%20fruit.%C2%A0Cavendish%20banana%20is%20under%20attack%20from%20a%20fungal%20infection%20called%20Panama%20disease%20(Fusarium%20wilt)%20tropical%20race%204.%20There%20are%20several%20varieties%20of%20bananas%2C%20but%20about%2047%20per%20cent%20that%20humans%20consume%20are%20Cavendish%20bananas.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNobody%20is%20even%20close%20to%20solving%20the%20problem%2C%26quot%3B%20Dan%20Koeppel%2C%20who%20wrote%20the%20book%20%26quot%3BBanana%3A%20The%20Fate%20of%20the%20Fruit%20That%20Changed%20the%20World%26quot%3B%2C%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.in%2Fscience%2Fnews%2Fcavendish-bananas-face-extinction-and-not-all-experts-agree-on-how-to-save-it%2Farticleshow%2F104626758.cms%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20fungal%20infection%20originates%20in%20the%20tree's%20roots%20and%20metastasizes%20to%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20plant.%20It%20prevents%20the%20plant%20from%20absorbing%20water%20or%20conducting%20photosynthesis.%20Eventually%2C%20the%20tree%20dies.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESome%20scientists%20are%20engaged%20in%20genetic%20modifications%20to%20enhance%20the%20fruit's%20disease%20resistance.%20However%2C%20there%20is%20an%20alternative%20viewpoint%20that%20suggests%20the%20ultimate%20remedy%20for%20this%20issue%20is%20for%20farmers%20to%20fundamentally%20transform%20banana%20production%20practices%2C%20moving%20away%20from%20exclusively%20cultivating%20a%20single%20fruit%20variety%2C%20the%20media%20outlet%20reported.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EInitially%20identified%20in%20Taiwan%20in%201989%2C%20Tropical%20Race%204%2C%20also%20known%20as%20TR4%2C%20has%20subsequently%20expanded%20its%20presence%20to%20Australia%2C%20followed%20by%20India%20and%20China%2C%20both%20major%20global%20banana%20producers.%20It%20has%20also%20made%20inroads%20into%20regions%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20and%20Africa.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EConcurrently%2C%20the%20disease%20has%20most%20recently%20surfaced%20in%20South%20America%2C%20as%20reported%20by%20James%20Dale%2C%20a%20professor%20leading%20the%20banana%20biotechnology%20program%20at%20Queensland%20University%20of%20Technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOnce%20it's%20in%20a%20country%20it's%20very%20hard%20to%20get%20rid%20of%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dan%20Bebber%2C%20a%20biosciences%20lecturer%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Exeter%2C%20in%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20fate%20currently%20befalling%20Cavendish%20bananas%20has%20previously%20afflicted%20another%20well-liked%20banana%20variety%20known%20as%20Gros%20Michel.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ETR4%20infected%20the%20banana%20variety%20in%201876%20and%20by%20the%201950s%20it%20was%20completely%20extinct.%20Farmers%20were%20forced%20to%20look%20for%20a%20new%20variety.%20In%20the%20following%20years%2C%20%26quot%3BCavendish%20became%20the%20leading%20export%20banana%20replacing%20Gros%20Michel%20because%20it%20was%20immune%20to%20TR1%2C%26quot%3B%20Dale%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20some%20plant%20pathologists%20believe%20that%20the%20Cavendish%20banana%20will%20not%20meet%20the%20same%20fate%20as%20Gros%20Michel.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20disease%20moves%20slowly%2C%20so%20we%20have%20at%20least%20a%20decade%20before%20the%20impact%20is%20drastic%2C%26quot%3B%20Dale%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EPotential%20remedies%20encompass%20genetically%20engineered%20strains%20that%20exhibit%20resistance%20to%20TR4%20and%20the%20practice%20of%20fruit%20grafting%2C%20which%20involves%20transferring%20tissues%20between%20plants%20to%20confer%20distinct%20attributes%2C%20such%20as%20resistance%20to%20disease.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cbr%3E%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698245820000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-10%2F1qdfs5hg_banana_625x300_17_October_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Fbananas-at-risk-of-extinction-due-to-fungus-outbreak-warn-scientists-4513517%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Cavendish%20banana%20is%20under%20attack%20from%20a%20fungal%20infection%20called%20Panama%20disease%20(Fusarium%20wilt)%20tropical%20race%204.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Fbananas-at-risk-of-extinction-due-to-fungus-outbreak-warn-scientists-4513517%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Fbananas-at-risk-of-extinction-due-to-fungus-outbreak-warn-scientists-4513517%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Ffeature%2Fbananas-at-risk-of-extinction-due-to-fungus-outbreak-warn-scientists-4513517%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Rallis%20India%20Q2%20results%3A%20PAT%20up%2013.88%25%20to%20Rs%2082%20crore%2C%20revenue%20down%2012.51%25%22%2C%22content%22%3A%