F25172749%2FKT-25-oct-sec-B.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EA%20foremost%20politician%20of%20the%20Palestine%20Authority%20says%20that%20the%20Hamas-Israel%20crisis%20will%20continue%20for%20months%20and%20get%20a%20lot%20worse%20before%20things%20calm%20down.%20Professor%20Ghassan%20Khatib%2C%20a%20former%20Palestine%20minister%20of%20labour%20and%20a%20former%20minister%20of%20planning%2C%20also%20fears%20that%20the%20situation%20could%20both%20increase%20the%20internal%20fragility%20and%20instability%20within%20Israel%20as%20well%20as%20spread%20across%20the%20region%2C%20creating%20a%20bigger%20conflict.%20He%20believes%20the%20onus%20is%20on%20what%20he%20calls%20Israel%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cbig%20brothers%E2%80%9D%20i.e.%20the%20US%20and%20major%20European%20countries%20like%20France%20and%20the%20United%20Kingdom%2C%20to%20increase%20pressure%20on%20Israel%20to%20first%20agree%20to%20a%20humanitarian%20pause%20and%20then%2C%20quickly%20thereafter%2C%20to%20a%20ceasefire.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20interview%20with%20Karan%20Thapar%20for%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Khatib%2C%20who%20is%20presently%20a%20professor%20of%20political%20science%20at%20Birzeit%20University%2C%20says%20the%20impact%20of%20the%20Hamas%20October%207%20attack%20has%20been%20to%20increase%20the%20popularity%20of%20Hamas%20whilst%20further%20reducing%20that%20of%20the%20Fatah%20(also%20known%20as%20the%20Palestinian%20National%20Liberation%20Movement)%20and%20further%20marginalising%20the%20Palestine%20Authority.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Khatib%20does%20not%20believe%20that%20the%20Hamas%20attack%20was%20primarily%20motivated%20by%20a%20desire%20to%20scupper%20the%20Israel-Saudi%20Arabia%20deal.%20That%20is%2C%20what%20he%20calls%2C%20collateral%20damage.%20He%20says%20the%20attack%20is%20explained%20by%20the%20internal%20Palestine%20situation%20and%20the%20treatment%20of%20the%20Palestinian%20people%2C%20both%20in%20the%20West%20Bank%20and%20Gaza%2C%20by%20successive%20Israeli%20governments%20and%2C%20in%20particular%2C%20that%20of%20Benjamin%20Netanyahu%20in%20the%20past%20couple%20of%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20emphatically%20states%20that%20a%20two-nation%20solution%20is%20the%20only%20viable%20and%20practical%20solution%20and%20he%20does%20not%20believe%20that%20the%20presence%20of%20750%2C000%20Israeli%20settlers%20in%20the%20West%20Bank%20is%20an%20insuperable%20obstacle.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20Khatib%20says%20a%20one-state%20solution%20is%20far%20too%20idealistic%20and%20very%20unlikely.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EKhatib%20believes%20that%20an%20exchange%20of%20hostages%20is%20most%20likely%20on%20the%20terms%20spelt%20out%20by%20Hamas%2C%20almost%20on%20the%20second%20day%2C%20i.e.%20an%20exchange%20for%20hostages%20for%20the%20return%20of%20all%20Palestinian%20prisoners%20in%20Israeli%20jails.%20There%20are%20said%20to%20be%20over%205%2C000%20such%20prisoners.%20He%20says%20such%20a%20disproportionate%20exchange%20is%20feasible%20because%2C%20in%202011%2C%20Netanyahu%20agreed%20to%20exchange%201%2C027%20Palestinian%20prisoners%20for%20a%20solitary%20Israel%20soldier.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ESee%20the%20full%20interview%20for%20the%20insights%20provided%20by%20Ghassan%20Khatib.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FpDv3SWxIqIA%3Fsi%3D66lRhDbKSsa2W7em%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698235346000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F25172749%2FKT-25-oct-sec-B.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fvideo%2Fwatch-gaza-israel-crisis-karan-thapar-ghassan-khatib%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20an%20interview%20with%20Karan%20Thapar%2C%20Ghassan%20Khatib%20says%20the%20onus%20is%20on%20the%20US%20and%20major%20European%20countries%20to%20increase%